Chicago American, Friday, April 6, 1962, p. 25, c. 1:

DALY DIARY

by Maggie Daly

"Eric ['The Counterfeit Traitor'] Erickson, onetime agent for the OSS in Stockholm arriving at O'Hare via American Airlines and being greeted by his former boss, Chicago Atty. Wilho Tikander, onetime director of the OSS in Scanivavia."

____________________________________

Chicago American, Saturday, April 28, 1962:

DOROTHY KILGALLEN

William Holden's newest film, "The Counterfeit Traitor," set a house record in the DeMille theater in its first week, and well may become bigger than the smash box office giant, "Psycho." The management is kept busy returning money to customers who buy tickets but can't get in. . . .

______________________________
